<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF2CFF66A7ADFCD6FEBCD897" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF2CFF66A7ADFCD6FEF0DF52" blockId="181.[189,310,825,851]" box="[189,310,825,851]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF2CFF66A7ADFCD6FEF0DF52" bold="true" box="[189,310,825,851]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A7ADFCD6FEF0DF52" bold="true" box="[189,310,825,851]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF2CFF66A7ADFC88FC6FD833" blockId="181.[189,1399,871,1074]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
This species may be separated from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF2CFF66A444FC87FC5EDF83" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[852,920,872,898]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A444FC87FC5EDF83" box="[852,920,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Southeast Asia and Oceania by the following combination of characters: cheliceral claw with four teeth and acute tooth in retrolateral row, adjacent to bifid tooth; pedipalp femur with five dorsal spines and four ventral spines (
<figureCitation id="9FD1BEE6FF2CFF66A3DFFC41FAACDFC9" box="[1231,1386,942,968]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="364.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[212,1382,265,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-51@364.[205,1382,265,1892]" captionTargetPageId="364" captionText="Fig. 109. Sarax dunni sp. nov. (NMNZ), general morphology, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp tarsus, frontal view. E. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A, E–F = 1 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5536695/files/figure.png" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Fig. 109E–F</figureCitation>
); pedipalp patella with five dorsal spines and four ventral spines (
<figureCitation id="9FD1BEE6FF2CFF66A4DAFC3EFBA0DFEA" box="[970,1126,977,1003]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="364.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[212,1382,265,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-51@364.[205,1382,265,1892]" captionTargetPageId="364" captionText="Fig. 109. Sarax dunni sp. nov. (NMNZ), general morphology, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp tarsus, frontal view. E. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A, E–F = 1 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5536695/files/figure.png" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Fig. 109E–F</figureCitation>
); leg IV basitibia with four pseudo-articles, trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A560FC1BFD41D80F" box="[624,647,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">bt</emphasis>
situated distally; leg IV distitibia trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A3C3FC1BFB29D80F" box="[1235,1263,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">bc</emphasis>
equidistant between 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A636FBF7FEFBD833" box="[294,317,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">bf</emphasis>
and s 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A691FBF7FE5ED833" box="[385,408,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">bf</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A6B7FBF7FE79D830" box="[423,447,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">sc</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A6E8FBF7FDCAD833" box="[504,524,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">sf</emphasis>
series each with five trichobothria.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF2CFF66A7ADFBB5FEBCD897" blockId="181.[189,1398,1113,1175]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF2CFF66A7ADFBB5FE8BD872" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,333,1113,1140]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dunni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A7ADFBB5FE8BD872" box="[189,333,1113,1140]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Sarax dunni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF2CFF66A645FBB5FE76D875" box="[341,432,1114,1140]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF2CFF66A526FBB5FD5ED872" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[566,664,1113,1140]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palau" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF2CFF66A526FBB5FD5ED872" box="[566,664,1113,1140]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">S. palau</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF2CFF66A5B0FBB5FD3BD875" box="[672,765,1114,1140]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from which it differs by the higher number of spines on the pedipalp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF2CFF66A7ADFB51FC1FD907" box="[189,985,1214,1287]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="etymology">
